There's a little-known feature with the JSONStorage where you can pass additional arguments to the TinyDB constructor which are passed through to the `json.dump()` method (see the note in [this section of the docs](http://tinydb.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage.html#storage-types)). Long story short, you could use something like this:

```python
db = TinyDB('db.json', sort_keys=True, indent=4, separators=(',', ': '))
db.insert({'b': 1})
db.insert({'a': 1})
```

That would result in a file like this:

```json
{
    "_default": {
        "1": {
            "b": 1
        },
        "2": {
            "a": 1
        }
    }
}
```

Hi @zorro765!

This was just discussed in issue [#1089](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/issues/1089#issuecomment-164092255) about 24 hours ago.

Basically, " and " and " or " ( both surrounded by spaces) are filter type key words which allow the user to query multiple words or filter types - e.g. "1 and 2", "1 or 2", ">10 and <100", etc.

These key words can be changed by [modifying the language](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-filter.html#localization).

```js
// change "and" & "or" filter key words to something else
$.tablesorter.language.and = "&&";
// these values are used inside of a new RegExp() so any special characters
// will need to be escaped
$.tablesorter.language.or = "\\|\\|";
```

