With the introduction of #34 first suggested variant works. Terminals should be written in separate section like:
```
STMT : STMT ADDOP STMT {left, 1}
     | STMT MULOP STMT {left, 1}
     | "(" STMT ")" | NUMBER;
ADDOP : "+" {1}
      | "-" {1};
MULOP : "*" {2}
      | "/" {2};

terminals
NUMBER: /\d+(.\d+)?/;
```

Please see [the tests](https://github.com/igordejanovic/parglare/blob/master/tests/func/regressions/test_issue_22_wrong_associativity_behaviour.py).

For the sort you can wrap the predicate with single quotes. For the search it will be trickier, the problem comes from https://github.com/lorenzofox3/Smart-Table/blob/master/src/stTable.js#L99 which is required for deep object search. But anyway I think you going into a difficult path. The point is that 
```Javascript
var object = {
   @foo : 'bar'
}
```
is not valid Javascript
and if 
```
var object = {
    "@foo": 'bar
};
```
then ``object.@foo`` is not and you'll have to use string accessor object['@foo'].

I think your best bet is to create an http interceptor which modify the keys of what the api send you. Or you can override the angular $parse service, but again it seems dangerous. There is nothing I can (or rather I want) to do on smart-table side for your use case, I am sorry

