@benjolitz I mean, it's a major version, you should expect some backwards compatibility to break, right?

In any case, I don't see `SetuptoolsVersion` anywhere in the documentation for version 38.x, and it is not in `pkg_resources.__all__`, so I don't think it was intended to be part of the public interface at this point. I think the preferred interface is to call `pkg_resources.parse_version` and use whatever object that gives you, rather than trying to manually construct any of these objects, which is why the changelog says "They should not have been used".

As for the other things, one of them is private (has a leading `_`) and the other one has the word "Legacy" in it, so those are pretty obviously deprecated. I think going forward just call `pkg_resources.parse_version()` or if for some reason you absolutely must directly construct these objects for some reason, use `pip install packaging`.

