@rbcarson Its all about user hashes - no microsoft client or server product will send user hashes in a v1 response. Having worked for Microsoft, the only reason edge facing products like IIS still permit incoming v1 is to support ancient 3rd party products build by firms that no longer exist. So if folks want to send their credentials in v1 hashes, the server will still accept them - it took yours.

