@dhermes 
would the implementation you described be able to provide a seek operation? The most commonly used methods in Python file objects are `read`, `seek`, `tell`, `readlines`, and `readline`. The first three alone are incredibly important for most programs that read indexed files.

Supporting file objects would also unblock appengine standard environment to appengine flexible environment migrations. If you recall, the standard environment has a `cloudstorage` library that gives file handles for GCS blobs. See the docs [here](https://cloud.google.com/appengine/docs/standard/python/googlecloudstorageclient/read-write-to-cloud-storage).

