This is not a bug with the python library, you just need to use a different query type. You need to use a `filtered` query:

so instead of 

    "query": {
      'filter': {'bool': {'must': [{'fquery': {'query': {'query_string': {'query': 'applicationType:("myapptype")'}}}}]}},
      'query': {'match': {'search_key': 'my_key_value'}},
      'aggs': {'client': {'terms': {'field': 'client'}}},
      'size': 0
    }

you need:

    "query": {
      "filtered": {
        'filter': {'bool': {'must': [{'fquery': {'query': {'query_string': {'query': 'applicationType:("myapptype")'}}}}]}},
        'query': {'match': {'search_key': 'my_key_value'}},
      },
      'aggs': {'client': {'terms': {'field': 'client'}}},
      'size': 0
    }

also note than in your case you probably want to change your filter from:

    {'bool': {'must': [{'fquery': {'query': {'query_string': {'query': 'applicationType:("myapptype")'}}}}]}}

to just:

    {'term': {'applicationType':"myapptype" }}

It will be faster and easier to understand. (note that this requires the field `applicationType` to be not analyzed)

Hope this helps

